This paper deals with the problem of balanced allocation, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of graphs in the problem formulation suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The study of maximum load and load balancing in the context of graphs suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) or network economics (cs.NE).
